<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-12-22T14:06:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-12-22T14:06:00-05:00" n="364" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d364">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">320/12–1451: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the United States Representative at the United Nations</hi>
                                    (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Austin</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-12-22T14:06:00-05:00">December 22, 1951—2:06 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <gloss target="#t_Gadel2">Gadel</gloss> 542. For Roosevelt and Cohen
                                from the Secretary. Re <gloss target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 665,
                                see <gloss target="#t_Gadel2">Gadel</gloss> 541, general conclusion
                                of which the Pres and I approved <pb facs="0515" n="493" xml:id="pg_493"/> after taking into consideration views which
                                you expressed. It seemed to Pres that this shld be handled by the
                                reps of the <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> countries to the
                                    <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss>. Pres felt Mrs. Roosevelt was
                                the ideal person to handle it for US.</p>
                            <p>We will inform Mrs. Roosevelt here if she has left Paris.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>